(LIGHT FURY WHINNIES. SQUAWKS)

991
00:50:03.582 --> 00:50:05.584
♪ ♪

992
00:50:09.789 --> 00:50:11.725
(LIGHT FURY PURRS)

993
00:50:18.664 --> 00:50:22.235
(BOTH PURRING SOFTLY)

994
00:50:24.869 --> 00:50:27.573
(GRUNTING SOFTLY)

995
00:50:31.876 --> 00:50:33.813
(WATER RUMBLING)

996
00:50:37.883 --> 00:50:39.819
(RUMBLING GROWS LOUDER)

997
00:50:41.553 --> 00:50:43.289
♪ ♪

998
00:50:47.360 --> 00:50:50.829
(BOTH GRUNTING)

999
00:50:59.704 --> 00:51:01.537
(CROWD CHEERING.
FESTIVE MUSIC PLAYING)

1000
00:51:01.539 --> 00:51:03.439
- To the chief! (WHOOPS)
- (LAUGHS)

1001
00:51:03.441 --> 00:51:04.742
GROUP:
To the chief!

1002
00:51:04.744 --> 00:51:07.010
- Aye. To our chief.
- (CROWD CHEERS)

1003
00:51:07.012 --> 00:51:09.046
- Oh. a chip off the old block.
- (HICCUP CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY)

1004
00:51:09.048 --> 00:51:12.015
Yeah. okay. guys.
Now I'm just getting sick.

1005
00:51:12.017 --> 00:51:13.783
Okay. (CHUCKLES)

1006
00:51:13.785 --> 00:51:15.686
- (RETCHES)
- Got to say.

1007
00:51:15.688 --> 00:51:17.521
I thought you were
well off your rocker.

1008
00:51:17.523 --> 00:51:19.689
but this spot ain't half bad.

1009
00:51:19.691 --> 00:51:22.559
This was supposed to be
a temporary solution.

1010
00:51:22.561 --> 00:51:23.526
It's unanimous.

1011
00:51:23.528 --> 00:51:26.296
Everyone agrees
we've definitely traded up.

1012
00:51:26.298 --> 00:51:28.666
- Well done. Chief.
- (FORCED CHUCKLE)

1013
00:51:28.668 --> 00:51:30.334
What if the tail broke?

1014
00:51:30.336 --> 00:51:31.934
- What if Grimmel found him?
- (SIGHS)

1015
00:51:31.936 --> 00:51:34.537
- What if he needs me?
- Would you relax?

1016
00:51:34.539 --> 00:51:36.707
He's probably having
the time of his life.

1017
00:51:36.709 --> 00:51:38.941
How would I know?
She never comes around.

1018
00:51:38.943 --> 00:51:41.412
And when she does.
she's always rushing off.

1019
00:51:41.414 --> 00:51:43.847
- I'm saying how-how do we know
- (GROANS)

1020
00:51:43.849 --> 00:51:45.515
if she's right for us?

1021
00:51:45.517 --> 00:51:47.517
- Us?
- You know what I mean.

1022
00:51:47.519 --> 00:51:50.387
She's so wild and skittish.
I'm just gonna say it.

1023
00:51:50.389 --> 00:51:51.555
I don't trust her.

1024
00:51:51.557 --> 00:51:54.358
(LAUGHS)
Can't tame 'em all. Hiccup.

1025
00:51:54.360 --> 00:51:56.859
One day. you'll have to snip
those apron strings

1026
00:51:56.861 --> 00:51:59.028
and let Toothless
stretch his wings.

1027
00:51:59.030 --> 00:52:02.099
Reminds me of a talk I had
with Stoick about you.

1028
00:52:02.101 --> 00:52:03.100
(SCREAMS)

1029
00:52:03.102 --> 00:52:04.401
(SNORTING)

1030
00:52:04.403 --> 00:52:06.336
Where do they keep coming from?

1031
00:52:06.338 --> 00:52:08.905
- Who?
- Those bloody Hobgobblers.

1032
00:52:08.907 --> 00:52:11.541
I swear they're popping up
faster than rabbits.

1033
00:52:11.543 --> 00:52:13.544
I think they want to eat me.

1034
00:52:13.546 --> 00:52:15.745
Evidence would suggest
I'm tasty.

1035
00:52:15.747 --> 00:52:17.414
Hiccy. a moment?

1036
00:52:17.416 --> 00:52:20.416
Listen. I've been
watching you walk. (SIGHS)

1037
00:52:20.418 --> 00:52:22.486
Lose the limp.
No one's gonna marry that.

1038
00:52:22.488 --> 00:52:24.354
- (CHUCKLES)
- I have a prosthetic leg.

1039
00:52:24.356 --> 00:52:26.523
- So have I.
- And I have a parasitic twin.

1040
00:52:26.525 --> 00:52:28.925
but you don't see me
limping around about it.

1041
00:52:28.927 --> 00:52:31.928
Come on. Chin up. Hiccy.
Puff out that chest.

1042
00:52:31.930 --> 00:52:34.530
- Move that butt to the left a little bit.
- (SLAPS)

1043
00:52:34.532 --> 00:52:37.533
(HOBGOBBLERS SNARLING.
GOBBER SCREAMS)

1044
00:52:37.535 --> 00:52:40.370
(CLOUDJUMPER ROARS.
CROWD CHATTERING)

1045
00:52:40.372 --> 00:52:42.705
(CLOUDJUMPER EXHALES HEAVILY)

1046
00:52:42.707 --> 00:52:45.475
Mom. are you hurt?
W-What happened out there?

1047
00:52:45.477 --> 00:52:47.745
I don't know how.
but Grimmel is tracking us.

1048
00:52:47.747 --> 00:52:51.615
Ah! This is all because
of the Hobgobblers.

1049
00:52:51.617 --> 00:52:53.716
He has a hundred ships.
maybe more.

1050
00:52:53.718 --> 00:52:56.720
with enough cages
for all of our dragons.

1051
00:52:56.722 --> 00:52:58.055
(SIGHS)

1052
00:52:58.057 --> 00:52:59.756
If Grimmel is
leading them here.

1053
00:52:59.758 --> 00:53:01.825
we have to take him
out of the mix.

1054
00:53:01.827 --> 00:53:04.660
Uh. and how would we do that?

1055
00:53:04.662 --> 00:53:06.662
By going there to capture him.

1056
00:53:06.664 --> 00:53:08.832
Capture him?

1057
00:53:08.834 --> 00:53:10.770
I'm with him! Who else?!

1058
00:53:12.003 --> 00:53:13.939
(HUMMING A TUNE)

1059
00:53:16.075 --> 00:53:18.511
(DRAGON SNORING)

1060
00:53:22.914 --> 00:53:24.851
(WIND WHISTLING SOFTLY)

1061
00:53:43.968 --> 00:53:46.637
(DRAGONS GROWLING)

1062
00:53:46.639 --> 00:53:48.638
(SNAPS FINGERS. DRAGONS SNARL)

1063
00:53:48.640 --> 00:53:49.943
(GROWLING)

1064
00:53:57.450 --> 00:54:01.151
(QUIETLY): Okay. split up.
We'll be harder to catch.

1065
00:54:01.153 --> 00:54:03.720
I was thinking we should
split up. just because.

1066
00:54:03.722 --> 00:54:05.955
I like your instincts.

1067
00:54:05.957 --> 00:54:07.691
What is this?

1068
00:54:07.693 --> 00:54:08.995
(GROWLING SOFTLY)

1069
00:54:11.831 --> 00:54:13.466
(GROWLING)

1070
00:54:15.066 --> 00:54:17.003
(ROCK CLATTERS)

1071
00:54:18.070 --> 00:54:19.805
(GASPING. GRUNTS)

1072
00:54:21.639 --> 00:54:23.542
(SNARLS)

1073
00:54:31.650 --> 00:54:33.586
♪ ♪

1074
00:54:39.825 --> 00:54:41.992
(HEAVY RUMBLING. HICCUP GASPS)

1075
00:54:41.994 --> 00:54:45.030
(METAL RATTLING)

1076
00:54:46.798 --> 00:54:49.666
- (FISHMEAT SQUEALING)
- Shh! Shh! Quiet.

1077
00:54:49.668 --> 00:54:51.234
- Quiet.
- GRIMMEL: Where's your dragon

1078
00:54:51.236 --> 00:54:54.171
when you need him. hmm. Chief?

1079
00:54:54.173 --> 00:54:57.774
Must have forgotten
all about you. (CHUCKLES)

1080
00:54:57.776 --> 00:54:59.843
First rule of the hunt:

1081
00:54:59.845 --> 00:55:02.278
separate the prey
from its pack.

1082
00:55:02.280 --> 00:55:06.283
You've just removed yourselves
from the equation.

1083
00:55:06.285 --> 00:55:08.184
- Why are you doing this?
- Really?

1084
00:55:08.186 --> 00:55:10.988
I didn't think you cared.

1085
00:55:10.990 --> 00:55:13.756
Well. unlike you.
when I was a boy

1086
00:55:13.758 --> 00:55:17.827
and I came upon a Night Fury.
I killed it where it slept.

1087
00:55:17.829 --> 00:55:22.265
That simple act of courage
made me a hero in my village.

1088
00:55:22.267 --> 00:55:25.801
So I decided
to kill every last one.

1089
00:55:25.803 --> 00:55:29.273
bringing real peace
to the people of this world.

1090
00:55:29.275 --> 00:55:31.274
Until you came along.

1091
00:55:31.276 --> 00:55:34.544
preaching that dragons
are something other than

1092
00:55:34.546 --> 00:55:36.713
thieves and murderers.

1093
00:55:36.715 --> 00:55:38.048
(SCOFFS)

1094
00:55:38.050 --> 00:55:41.584
That nonsense dies now.
starting with you.

1095
00:55:41.586 --> 00:55:43.887
- But you have dragons of your own.
- (LAUGHS)

1096
00:55:43.889 --> 00:55:45.988
- (LAUGHS): These?
- (GROWLING)

1097
00:55:45.990 --> 00:55:47.990
They're dragon killers.

1098
00:55:47.992 --> 00:55:51.260
drugged into obedience
with their own venom.

1099
00:55:51.262 --> 00:55:54.597
Not even your precious alpha
could control them.

1100
00:55:54.599 --> 00:55:57.934
They serve me and only me.

1101
00:55:57.936 --> 00:56:00.303
Allow me to demonstrate.
(WHISTLES)

1102
00:56:00.305 --> 00:56:02.104
Take cover!

1103
00:56:02.106 --> 00:56:04.177
(DRAGONS SNARLING)

1104
00:56:06.278 --> 00:56:08.077
- Split up!
- (GRUNTS)

1105
00:56:08.079 --> 00:56:09.515
Whoa!

1106
00:56:11.082 --> 00:56:12.017
(GRUNTING)

1107
00:56:14.686 --> 00:56:16.622
- Whoa! Run!
- (SNARLING)

1108
00:56:18.923 --> 00:56:19.957
(PANTING)

1109
00:56:19.959 --> 00:56:22.258
(GRUNTS)

1110
00:56:22.260 --> 00:56:24.130
- (SHOUTS. GRUNTS)
- (DRAGON ROARS)

1111
00:56:26.231 --> 00:56:28.167
(VALKA GRUNTING)

1112
00:56:34.606 --> 00:56:36.208
Up here!

1113
00:56:38.276 --> 00:56:39.309
(GASPS)

1114
00:56:39.311 --> 00:56:40.977
(TAIL RATTLES)

1115
00:56:40.979 --> 00:56:41.914
(GRUNTING)

1116
00:56:46.050 --> 00:56:48.151
(DRAGON SQUEALS)

1117
00:56:48.153 --> 00:56:49.622
(ROARS)

1118
00:56:52.057 --> 00:56:53.993
- Hurry!
- (GRUNTING)

1119
00:56:55.927 --> 00:56:57.894
Go. go. go. go. go!

1120
00:56:57.896 --> 00:56:59.896
(PANTING)

1121
00:56:59.898 --> 00:57:01.166
Hiccup!

1122
00:57:04.903 --> 00:57:06.403
(DRAGON ROARS)

1123
00:57:06.405 --> 00:57:08.070
Gotcha.

1124
00:57:08.072 --> 00:57:09.740
Go. Cloudjumper!

1125
00:57:09.742 --> 00:57:11.678
(DRAGONS ROARING)

1126
00:57:15.046 --> 00:57:17.046
Yeah!

1127
00:57:17.048 --> 00:57:18.985
- Our hero!
- (CLOUDJUMPER ROARS)

1128
00:57:20.952 --> 00:57:23.954
(DRAGONS ROARING)

1129
00:57:23.956 --> 00:57:25.892
(HEAVY RUMBLING)

1130
00:57:27.860 --> 00:57:30.794
(DRAGONS CALLING.
FISHMEAT SQUEALING)

1131
00:57:30.796 --> 00:57:32.162
(SIGHS):
Hmm.

1132
00:57:32.164 --> 00:57:34.934
Ugh. he takes
that stupid baby everywhere.

1133
00:57:37.269 --> 00:57:40.269
(DRAGONS CALLING)

1134
00:57:40.271 --> 00:57:41.972
GOBBER:
God almighty!

1135
00:57:41.974 --> 00:57:43.907
Guess we won't be
needing this then. huh?

1136
00:57:43.909 --> 00:57:46.175
I led us right into his trap.

1137
00:57:46.177 --> 00:57:49.379
Yeah. nice work. Chief.
Right. Ruff?

1138
00:57:49.381 --> 00:57:50.914
Wait.

1139
00:57:50.916 --> 00:57:52.381
- Uh...
- Where is Ruffnut?

1140
00:57:52.383 --> 00:57:54.251
We-we left her behind?

1141
00:57:54.253 --> 00:57:56.285
How could you not notice
she was missing?

1142
00:57:56.287 --> 00:57:58.120
You ride a two-headed dragon.

1143
00:57:58.122 --> 00:57:59.289
Oh. yeah.

1144
00:57:59.291 --> 00:58:02.392
I feel like how Ruffnut is
every day: dumb.

1145
00:58:02.394 --> 00:58:04.227
Odin be spanked!

1146
00:58:04.229 --> 00:58:06.329
This just gets
better and better.

1147
00:58:06.331 --> 00:58:07.863
- (OTHERS GRUMBLING)
- Any more fantastic news?

1148
00:58:07.865 --> 00:58:09.198
TUFFNUT:
I try to avoid looking at her.

1149
00:58:09.200 --> 00:58:10.733
It gives me acid reflux.

1150
00:58:10.735 --> 00:58:12.936
O-Okay. guys.
just keep your helmets on.

1151
00:58:12.938 --> 00:58:14.403
Toothless and I will find her.

1152
00:58:14.405 --> 00:58:16.338
Toothless has
the Light Fury now.

1153
00:58:16.340 --> 00:58:18.108
He's probably
not even coming back.

1154
00:58:18.110 --> 00:58:19.341
What?

1155
00:58:19.343 --> 00:58:21.343
You gave him
his freedom. Hiccup.

1156
00:58:21.345 --> 00:58:23.245
What were you expecting?

1157
00:58:23.247 --> 00:58:25.115
I never thought
he'd stay away for good!

1158
00:58:25.117 --> 00:58:27.850
I-I... (SIGHS)

1159
00:58:27.852 --> 00:58:31.256
Look. I'll-I'll figure it out.
I just need more time.

1160
00:58:32.858 --> 00:58:35.791
He thinks he has to lead alone.

1161
00:58:35.793 --> 00:58:39.329
Well. because
his father had to.

1162
00:58:39.331 --> 00:58:42.932
He doesn't realize
the strength you have together.

1163
00:58:42.934 --> 00:58:46.336
- Do you still believe in him?
- Of course.

1164
00:58:46.338 --> 00:58:48.137
I wish he did.

1165
00:58:48.139 --> 00:58:52.508
But he thinks he's nothing
without Toothless.

1166
00:58:52.510 --> 00:58:55.180
Then help him
realize the truth.

1167
00:58:58.282 --> 00:58:59.816
(STORMFLY SQUAWKS)

1168
00:58:59.818 --> 00:59:00.983
- Get on.
- What?

1169
00:59:00.985 --> 00:59:02.218
We're going to find him.

1170
00:59:02.220 --> 00:59:04.454
Really?

1171
00:59:04.456 --> 00:59:07.758
- (STORMFLY SNARLS)
- Everybody. stay put.

1172
00:59:07.760 --> 00:59:10.459
We will get Ruffnut back.
Don't worry.

1173
00:59:10.461 --> 00:59:12.129
(SCOFFS) Worry?

1174
00:59:12.131 --> 00:59:14.930
If they're stuck with Ruffnut.
I'm more worried about them.

1175
00:59:14.932 --> 00:59:16.832
(CHUCKLES)

1176
00:59:16.834 --> 00:59:20.336
Why the long face?
(LAUGHS)

1177
00:59:20.338 --> 00:59:22.405
I mean. mine's long.
but yours is really long.

1178
00:59:22.407 --> 00:59:25.175
All face and no brain. like
you got stretched at birth.

1179
00:59:25.177 --> 00:59:26.776
Do you have a twin. too?

1180
00:59:26.778 --> 00:59:28.512
Tuffnut took up all the room
in Mom's belly.

1181
00:59:28.514 --> 00:59:30.379
Otherwise I'd have
a rounder head and more brains.

1182
00:59:30.381 --> 00:59:32.515
- That's science.
- (GROANS)

1183
00:59:32.517 --> 00:59:34.917
My braids are like
little Zipplebacks. See?

1184
00:59:34.919 --> 00:59:36.919
(IMITATES DRAGONS ROARING)

1185
00:59:36.921 --> 00:59:39.289
Even the mold spots
look like eyes. It's so cute.

1186
00:59:39.291 --> 00:59:40.990
They even have
little horns and everything.

1187
00:59:40.992 --> 00:59:42.325
just like Barf and Belch.

1188
00:59:42.327 --> 00:59:44.026
Except me and Barf
can't stand Belch.

1189
00:59:44.028 --> 00:59:45.227
so they're really just Barfs.

1190
00:59:45.229 --> 00:59:46.296
It's warm in here.

1191
00:59:46.298 --> 00:59:48.465
I know what you're thinking.

1192
00:59:48.467 --> 00:59:51.267
You've never had
a prisoner this hot.

1193
00:59:51.269 --> 00:59:53.068
All the boys love me.

1194
00:59:53.070 --> 00:59:55.204
Except Eret.
who totally lost his chance.

1195
00:59:55.206 --> 00:59:57.240
That ship has sailed. boy.
Sorry.

1196
00:59:57.242 --> 00:59:58.575
And Hiccup is
practically married

1197
00:59:58.577 --> 00:59:59.742
to that round-head. Astrid.

1198
00:59:59.744 --> 01:00:03.113
But Snotlout and Fishlegs.
they're basically my harem.

1199
01:00:03.115 --> 01:00:05.515
- (GROANS. SIGHS)
- I just can't choose. you know?

1200
01:00:05.517 --> 01:00:08.117
Snotlout's a beefcake but
almost too pretty. you know?

1201
01:00:08.119 --> 01:00:10.452
Sometimes I think he's more
in love with himself than me.

1202
01:00:10.454 --> 01:00:13.823
There's only room for one
beauty in this relationship.

1203
01:00:13.825 --> 01:00:16.392
(CHUCKLES) Fishlegs would keep
me alive longer if I had to

1204
01:00:16.394 --> 01:00:18.227
eat one of them. stranded
on some glacier somewhere.

1205
01:00:18.229 --> 01:00:20.030
- But he never shuts up about dragons.
- (DRAGON GROANS)

1206
01:00:20.032 --> 01:00:21.430
Don't you hate
when people never stop talking?

1207
01:00:21.432 --> 01:00:23.332
- Yes. I do.
- They just keep going and going.

1208
01:00:23.334 --> 01:00:25.836
Blah. blah. blah.
It's so boring.

1209
01:00:25.838 --> 01:00:27.838
- Can't we just feed her to your dragons?
- I'm hungry.

1210
01:00:27.840 --> 01:00:29.238
Hey. what do you have
to eat around here?

1211
01:00:29.240 --> 01:00:30.506
I'm allergic to fish.
You should know that.

1212
01:00:30.508 --> 01:00:33.843
That's all they have
at that stupid new island.

1213
01:00:33.845 --> 01:00:35.412
Do you have any clams?

1214
01:00:35.414 --> 01:00:37.247
They're like little mouths
with slimy food inside

1215
01:00:37.249 --> 01:00:39.349
that's already chewed.
like the way Mom used to do it.

1216
01:00:39.351 --> 01:00:42.519
- (CHUCKLES) - Enough!
- (DRAGON SNARLS)

1217
01:00:42.521 --> 01:00:44.954
Until I turned 12 and she was
like. "Chew your own food."

1218
01:00:44.956 --> 01:00:46.523
And I was like.
"No. I kinda like it."

1219
01:00:46.525 --> 01:00:49.258
Most annoying creature
ever to cross my path.

1220
01:00:49.260 --> 01:00:51.061
(GASPS) Aw.

1221
01:00:51.063 --> 01:00:54.164
Oops. you let the dragons out.

1222
01:00:54.166 --> 01:00:56.032
I'm gonna get you.
I'm gonna get you.

1223
01:00:56.034 --> 01:00:57.867
- No. this one's gonna get you. (LAUGHS)
- Get...

1224
01:00:57.869 --> 01:01:00.202
Take him and go!

1225
01:01:00.204 --> 01:01:02.939
Please! I beg you!

1226
01:01:02.941 --> 01:01:05.341
The Deathgrippers
will have to forgo dinner.

1227
01:01:05.343 --> 01:01:08.611
Ew. you feed
your dragons dragons?

1228
01:01:08.613 --> 01:01:10.914
- Go!
- Where's your bathroom?

1229
01:01:10.916 --> 01:01:12.015
I got to...
(CLICKS TONGUE)

1230
01:01:12.017 --> 01:01:14.316
Okay! Gods.

1231
01:01:14.318 --> 01:01:17.387
- No wonder you have gray hair.
- (DRAGON GROANS)

1232
01:01:17.389 --> 01:01:19.256
Stress is not good for you.

1233
01:01:19.258 --> 01:01:21.124
(LAUGHS)

1234
01:01:21.126 --> 01:01:23.062
So long. losers!

1235
01:01:26.131 --> 01:01:28.067
(STORMFLY GRUNTING SOFTLY)

1236
01:01:32.970 --> 01:01:35.604
- Where-where is she heading?
- She's tracking something.

1237
01:01:35.606 --> 01:01:37.539
- Aren't you. girl?
- (SNARLS)

1238
01:01:37.541 --> 01:01:40.542
There's nothing but
miles and miles of...

1239
01:01:40.544 --> 01:01:42.544
(WATER RUSHING)

1240
01:01:42.546 --> 01:01:44.483
♪ ♪

1241
01:01:53.624 --> 01:01:55.561
♪ ♪

1242
01:02:12.077 --> 01:02:14.209
A great waterfall.

1243
01:02:14.211 --> 01:02:16.646
- At the end of the world.
- (STORMFLY SNARLS)

1244
01:02:16.648 --> 01:02:18.515
(HICCUP AND ASTRID SCREAM)

1245
01:02:18.517 --> 01:02:20.453
ASTRID (ECHOING):
Stormfly!

1246
01:02:25.222 --> 01:02:27.159
(HICCUP AND ASTRID PANTING)

1247
01:02:31.363 --> 01:02:33.299
♪ ♪

1248
01:02:42.573 --> 01:02:44.175
(SNIFFING)

1249
01:02:46.244 --> 01:02:48.180
(SNORTING)

1250
01:02:52.184 --> 01:02:54.120
(SNORTING SOFTLY. SNIFFING)

1251
01:03:04.296 --> 01:03:06.232
♪ ♪

1252
01:03:16.207 --> 01:03:18.207
(CHUCKLES):
Wow.

1253
01:03:18.209 --> 01:03:20.146
Look.

1254
01:03:29.121 --> 01:03:31.057
♪ ♪

1255
01:03:48.072 --> 01:03:50.506
(WINGS FLUTTERING)

1256
01:03:50.508 --> 01:03:52.445
(BOTH GASPING)

1257
01:03:54.412 --> 01:03:56.514
- Wow.
- Wow.

1258
01:04:02.521 --> 01:04:04.457
♪ ♪

1259
01:04:10.327 --> 01:04:11.329
(ASTRID GASPS)

1260
01:04:13.432 --> 01:04:15.368
(DRAGONS CALLING)

1261
01:04:23.108 --> 01:04:25.477
(DRAGON CALLING)

1262
01:04:30.682 --> 01:04:33.151
(STORMFLY SQUAWKS. SNORTS)

1263
01:04:36.354 --> 01:04:38.854
It really does exist.

1264
01:04:38.856 --> 01:04:40.793
(DRAGONS CALLING)

1265
01:04:44.195 --> 01:04:46.131
♪ ♪

1266
01:04:56.273 --> 01:04:59.108
- Toothless.
- Shh. You'll spook them.

1267
01:04:59.110 --> 01:05:01.046
(DRAGONS CONTINUE CALLING)

1268
01:05:10.122 --> 01:05:13.059
(ROARING)

1269
01:05:16.193 --> 01:05:18.130
(DRAGONS CONTINUE CALLING)

1270
01:05:28.506 --> 01:05:30.443
(DRAGONS ROARING LOUDLY)

1271
01:05:36.881 --> 01:05:38.717
(ROARING LOUDLY)

1272
01:05:41.452 --> 01:05:44.556
Now. that's a king.

1273
01:05:50.494 --> 01:05:52.430
(LIGHT FURY PURRS SOFTLY)

1274
01:05:58.769 --> 01:06:00.706
(BOTH CALLING SOFTLY)

1275
01:06:03.307 --> 01:06:05.244
(LIGHT FURY PURRS)

1276
01:06:06.410 --> 01:06:08.347
♪ ♪

1277
01:06:26.264 --> 01:06:28.530
- We should go.
- (DRAGON GROWLING)

1278
01:06:28.532 --> 01:06:31.466
BOTH:
Oh. no.

1279
01:06:31.468 --> 01:06:33.805
(ASTRID GRUNTING AND PANTING)

1280
01:06:35.340 --> 01:06:36.542
(ROARING)

1281
01:06:38.476 --> 01:06:40.642
(DRAGONS GROWLING)

1282
01:06:40.644 --> 01:06:42.912
Stormfly!

1283
01:06:42.914 --> 01:06:44.713
(BOTH GRUNTING)

1284
01:06:44.715 --> 01:06:46.751
(TOOTHLESS CALLING)

1285
01:06:48.653 --> 01:06:49.919
(GRUNTS)

1286
01:06:49.921 --> 01:06:51.653
(DRAGONS GROWLING)

1287
01:06:51.655 --> 01:06:53.224
(GRUNTING AND PANTING)

1288
01:06:55.693 --> 01:06:57.693
(HICCUP SCREAMS)

1289
01:06:57.695 --> 01:06:58.727
(BOTH GRUNT)

1290
01:06:58.729 --> 01:07:01.666
- Go! Go!
- (PANTING)

1291
01:07:05.604 --> 01:07:06.539
(ROARS)

1292
01:07:08.506 --> 01:07:09.909
(HICCUP PANTING)

1293
01:07:12.543 --> 01:07:14.544
I-I'm sorry. bud.
I-I just...

1294
01:07:14.546 --> 01:07:15.481
(TOOTHLESS ROARS)

1295
01:07:19.851 --> 01:07:21.486
(STORMFLY SQUAWKS)

1296
01:07:24.521 --> 01:07:26.457
♪ ♪

1297
01:07:33.298 --> 01:07:35.801
(STOICK SNIFFLES)

1298
01:07:37.936 --> 01:07:39.501
(HICCUP GRUNTS SOFTLY)

1299
01:07:39.503 --> 01:07:41.637
Son.

1300
01:07:41.639 --> 01:07:42.805
(SNIFFLES)

1301
01:07:42.807 --> 01:07:44.474
You should be asleep.

1302
01:07:44.476 --> 01:07:46.778
I was thirsty.

1303
01:07:47.878 --> 01:07:49.879
(SIGHS)

1304
01:07:49.881 --> 01:07:51.617
Yeah. come here.

1305
01:07:56.521 --> 01:07:58.457
(STOICK GRUNTS. SIGHS)

1306
01:08:02.860 --> 01:08:05.294
Dad?

1307
01:08:05.296 --> 01:08:08.930
Are you gonna get us a new mom?

1308
01:08:08.932 --> 01:08:11.901
(STOICK SIGHS. KISSES)

1309
01:08:11.903 --> 01:08:13.635
I don't want another.

1310
01:08:13.637 --> 01:08:17.873
Your mom was
the only woman for me.

1311
01:08:17.875 --> 01:08:20.545
She was the love of my life.

1312
01:08:22.479 --> 01:08:26.682
But with love comes loss. son.

1313
01:08:26.684 --> 01:08:28.551
It's part of the deal.

1314
01:08:28.553 --> 01:08:33.291
Sometimes it hurts. but
in the end. it's all worth it.

1315
01:08:35.994 --> 01:08:39.462
There's no greater gift
than love.

1316
01:08:39.464 --> 01:08:41.400
(SIGHS)

1317
01:08:44.902 --> 01:08:46.838
(TOOTHLESS GROANING SADLY)

1318
01:09:03.655 --> 01:09:06.122
(TOOTHLESS GROANING SADLY)

1319
01:09:06.124 --> 01:09:09.528
♪ ♪

1320
01:09:14.965 --> 01:09:17.499
(GROANS SADLY)

1321
01:09:17.501 --> 01:09:19.437
(HICCUP SIGHS)

1322
01:09:21.772 --> 01:09:24.039
It's okay. bud.

1323
01:09:24.041 --> 01:09:26.445
You belong there. with her.

1324
01:09:28.146 --> 01:09:29.645
We don't.

1325
01:09:29.647 --> 01:09:32.013
(GRUNTS SOFTLY)

1326
01:09:32.015 --> 01:09:35.450
And that's all right.

1327
01:09:35.452 --> 01:09:37.753
- We'll find a way to man...
- (DRAGON CALLS IN DISTANCE)

1328
01:09:37.755 --> 01:09:39.023
(GRUNTS)

1329
01:09:41.992 --> 01:09:42.928
(GRUNTS HAPPILY)

1330
01:09:46.930 --> 01:09:48.597
- Hey!
- (CHUFFING)

1331
01:09:48.599 --> 01:09:49.766
(LAUGHS)

1332
01:09:49.768 --> 01:09:53.535
She followed us back!

1333
01:09:53.537 --> 01:09:56.838
(BOTH PURRING HAPPILY)

1334
01:09:56.840 --> 01:09:59.977
We might not have to
say good-bye after all.

1335
01:10:04.616 --> 01:10:07.449
(BOTH PURRING)

1336
01:10:07.451 --> 01:10:08.784
That's it.

1337
01:10:08.786 --> 01:10:10.586
RUFFNUT:
Woo-hoo! Yeah! (LAUGHS)

1338
01:10:10.588 --> 01:10:12.622
- Ruffnut?
- Miss me?

1339
01:10:12.624 --> 01:10:14.090
How did you escape?

1340
01:10:14.092 --> 01:10:15.824
I annoyed them
till they let me go.

1341
01:10:15.826 --> 01:10:17.493
- (LAUGHS)
- Wait. Wait.

1342
01:10:17.495 --> 01:10:20.596
- Grimmel let you go?
- So dumb.

1343
01:10:20.598 --> 01:10:22.597
They couldn't handle me.

1344
01:10:22.599 --> 01:10:24.600
See. everyone thinks
Tuffnut's more annoying. but...

1345
01:10:24.602 --> 01:10:26.903
- Wait. hold on.
- Ruffnut. focus.

1346
01:10:26.905 --> 01:10:28.770
- Were you followed?
- (RUFFNUT SCOFFS SOFTLY)

1347
01:10:28.772 --> 01:10:30.840
I never look back. Hiccup.

1348
01:10:30.842 --> 01:10:32.941
(GASPS) Toothless.

1349
01:10:32.943 --> 01:10:35.444
- (GRUNTING)
- Toothless!

1350
01:10:35.446 --> 01:10:37.615
(SNIFFS. ROARS)

1351
01:10:40.018 --> 01:10:42.517
(YELPS)

1352
01:10:42.519 --> 01:10:43.718
(GRUNTS)

1353
01:10:43.720 --> 01:10:46.588
(LIGHT FURY SQUEALING)

1354
01:10:46.590 --> 01:10:48.393
Toothless. come back!

1355
01:10:52.563 --> 01:10:54.066
(GROWLS)

1356
01:10:55.700 --> 01:10:56.833
(ROARS)

1357
01:10:56.835 --> 01:10:58.170
No!

1358
01:11:01.138 --> 01:11:02.707
(DRAGONS SQUAWKING)

1359
01:11:14.818 --> 01:11:19.654
And now our little game
must come to an end.

1360
01:11:19.656 --> 01:11:21.592
(DRAGONS ROARING)

1361
01:11:23.928 --> 01:11:25.794
Call them off. alpha!

1362
01:11:25.796 --> 01:11:28.599
No reason for her to die. too.

1363
01:11:32.704 --> 01:11:34.173
(DRAGON GRUNTS)

1364
01:11:35.639 --> 01:11:37.175
(ROARS)

1365
01:11:38.776 --> 01:11:40.711
(ROARING STOPS)

1366
01:11:41.812 --> 01:11:43.078
What are they doing?

1367
01:11:43.080 --> 01:11:46.815
- They could totally take him.
- Not with her life on the line.

1368
01:11:46.817 --> 01:11:50.019
(TOOTHLESS ROARING)

1369
01:11:50.021 --> 01:11:51.587
Save your breath.

1370
01:11:51.589 --> 01:11:54.891
The only alpha
they respond to is me.

1371
01:11:54.893 --> 01:11:56.829
(TOOTHLESS GROANING)

1372
01:11:59.863 --> 01:12:01.797
- (SIGHS)
- Oh...

1373
01:12:01.799 --> 01:12:04.699
don't feel too badly.
You tried your best.

1374
01:12:04.701 --> 01:12:09.605
But you are nothing
without your dragon.

1375
01:12:09.607 --> 01:12:12.077
(WHISTLES. DRAGONS GROWL)

1376
01:12:17.180 --> 01:12:19.181
(CALLS)

1377
01:12:19.183 --> 01:12:21.119
(DRAGONS CALLING)

1378
01:12:24.688 --> 01:12:26.055
Toothless!

1379
01:12:26.057 --> 01:12:27.593
(PANTING)

1380
01:12:32.996 --> 01:12:34.932
(DRAGONS CALLING)

1381
01:12:43.974 --> 01:12:46.208
Oh. that is
just (GROANS) great!

1382
01:12:46.210 --> 01:12:47.376
Now what?

1383
01:12:47.378 --> 01:12:50.946
I think it's time for number
two to become number one.

1384
01:12:50.948 --> 01:12:52.884
He'll listen to you.

1385
01:12:57.888 --> 01:13:00.155
- Don't say it.
- I wasn't going to.

1386
01:13:00.157 --> 01:13:01.891
I shouldn't have
dragged you out there.

1387
01:13:01.893 --> 01:13:04.126
He wouldn't have flown me back.
She wouldn't have followed.

1388
01:13:04.128 --> 01:13:06.127
- Yep.
- (FRUSTRATED GRUNT)

1389
01:13:06.129 --> 01:13:09.097
I feel like the same screwup
I was before I met Toothless.

1390
01:13:09.099 --> 01:13:10.932
I can see that.

1391
01:13:10.934 --> 01:13:13.101
Are you just gonna stand there
and agree with everything?

1392
01:13:13.103 --> 01:13:13.935
Well. you're right.

1393
01:13:13.937 --> 01:13:16.771
You're back
to where you started.

1394
01:13:16.773 --> 01:13:19.108
but I was the first
to believe in you.

1395
01:13:19.110 --> 01:13:20.810
And I have watched you doubt

1396
01:13:20.812 --> 01:13:23.279
whether you're worthy
ever since.

1397
01:13:23.281 --> 01:13:25.114
But you know what?

1398
01:13:25.116 --> 01:13:28.985
I am the person I am today
because of you.

1399
01:13:28.987 --> 01:13:32.053
I never told you that.
but it's true.

1400
01:13:32.055 --> 01:13:34.757
You are the bravest.
most stubborn.

1401
01:13:34.759 --> 01:13:38.761
most determined knucklehead
I know.

1402
01:13:38.763 --> 01:13:41.029
Toothless didn't
give you that. Hiccup.

1403
01:13:41.031 --> 01:13:44.367
- He just made it...
- Easier.

1404
01:13:44.369 --> 01:13:47.970
And now it's gonna be
a lot harder.

1405
01:13:47.972 --> 01:13:51.407
So. what are you
gonna do about it?

1406
01:13:51.409 --> 01:13:54.142
Probably something stupid.

1407
01:13:54.144 --> 01:13:56.915
That's the Hiccup I know.

1408
01:14:00.018 --> 01:14:02.918
Suit up. gang.
We're going to get them back.

1409
01:14:02.920 --> 01:14:05.921
- What?
- He's lost his mind.

1410
01:14:05.923 --> 01:14:09.025
Now. that's marriage material.

1411
01:14:09.027 --> 01:14:12.261
At last. faithful pupil.
you are ready.

1412
01:14:12.263 --> 01:14:17.432
Um. how are we gonna get our
dragons back without dragons?

1413
01:14:17.434 --> 01:14:18.801
Trust me.

1414
01:14:18.803 --> 01:14:20.738
(DRAGONS CALLING.
TRAPPERS CHATTERING)

1415
01:14:22.406 --> 01:14:24.873
- Watch yourselves.
- You're next.

1416
01:14:24.875 --> 01:14:26.441
(CHATTER CONTINUES)

1417
01:14:26.443 --> 01:14:27.810
Move it.

1418
01:14:27.812 --> 01:14:28.944
(ROARS)

1419
01:14:28.946 --> 01:14:30.680
(TOOTHLESS ROARS)

1420
01:14:30.682 --> 01:14:32.948
Um. that's right. alpha.

1421
01:14:32.950 --> 01:14:34.920
No surprises.

1422
01:14:36.920 --> 01:14:39.055
(TOOTHLESS CALLS)

1423
01:14:39.057 --> 01:14:40.388
(TRAPPERS GRUNTING)

1424
01:14:40.390 --> 01:14:43.292
(SNARLS)

1425
01:14:43.294 --> 01:14:48.864
So. jump off the cliff
in these.

1426
01:14:48.866 --> 01:14:50.365
That's the best you've got?

1427
01:14:50.367 --> 01:14:53.168
No. you guys are
the best I've got.

1428
01:14:53.170 --> 01:14:55.437
(GASPS) Aw.

1429
01:14:55.439 --> 01:14:57.205
- I'm with him! Who else?!
- I'm with...

1430
01:14:57.207 --> 01:14:59.240
Ruffnut. that was my line.

1431
01:14:59.242 --> 01:15:01.243
- HICCUP: Let's go!
- ASTRID: Try to keep up!

1432
01:15:01.245 --> 01:15:03.945
(HICCUP GRUNTS. ASTRID WHOOPS)

1433
01:15:03.947 --> 01:15:05.381
(WIND RUSHING)

1434
01:15:05.383 --> 01:15:06.949
- (WHOOPING)
- Yeah! - Yeah!

1435
01:15:06.951 --> 01:15:09.718
- I'm doing it!
- All right! - Oh!

1436
01:15:09.720 --> 01:15:10.985
- (TRAPPERS CHATTERING)
- GUARD: Get clear!

1437
01:15:10.987 --> 01:15:12.923
(TOOTHLESS GROANING)

1438
01:15:17.795 --> 01:15:19.794
(GROWLS. GASPS)

1439
01:15:19.796 --> 01:15:22.097
Aw. (LAUGHS)

1440
01:15:22.099 --> 01:15:24.266
You didn't think I'd actually
hand you the Night Fury.

1441
01:15:24.268 --> 01:15:25.266
did you?

1442
01:15:25.268 --> 01:15:26.968
He's mine to kill.

1443
01:15:26.970 --> 01:15:28.770
That snake!

1444
01:15:28.772 --> 01:15:31.474
I intend to finish
what I started.

1445
01:15:31.476 --> 01:15:35.810
Best of luck controlling them
without an alpha.

1446
01:15:35.812 --> 01:15:38.082
HICCUP (IN DISTANCE):
Hold on. Toothless!

1447
01:15:41.518 --> 01:15:43.886
- (TUFFNUT GASPING)
- RUFFNUT: Let go!

1448
01:15:43.888 --> 01:15:45.386
(SCREAMS) Could've used
some practice!

1449
01:15:45.388 --> 01:15:47.489
Ah. I should've
skipped breakfast!

1450
01:15:47.491 --> 01:15:49.758
(GASPING)

1451
01:15:49.760 --> 01:15:51.228
(GRUNTING)

1452
01:15:54.397 --> 01:15:56.265
(GRUNTING)

1453
01:15:56.267 --> 01:15:57.867
(PANTING)

1454
01:15:57.869 --> 01:15:59.301
Toothless!

1455
01:15:59.303 --> 01:16:01.470
(TOOTHLESS ROARS)

1456
01:16:01.472 --> 01:16:03.873
- Look out!
- (GUARDS SCREAMING)

1457
01:16:03.875 --> 01:16:05.908
Hot. hot. hot. hot!

1458
01:16:05.910 --> 01:16:07.810
(SCREAMING CONTINUES)

1459
01:16:07.812 --> 01:16:10.980
They're getting away!

1460
01:16:10.982 --> 01:16:12.314
(TOOTHLESS CALLS)

1461
01:16:12.316 --> 01:16:13.783
(CLOUDJUMPER CALLS)

1462
01:16:13.785 --> 01:16:15.885
(ALL GRUNTING)

1463
01:16:15.887 --> 01:16:18.988
(WHOOPS. GRUNTS)

1464
01:16:18.990 --> 01:16:20.021
(GROWLS)

1465
01:16:20.023 --> 01:16:22.291
Perfect timing.

1466
01:16:22.293 --> 01:16:24.959
- Put that down!
- I'll take the skinny one!

1467
01:16:24.961 --> 01:16:25.961
Game faces!

1468
01:16:25.963 --> 01:16:28.797
Yeah. what are you waiting for?
Get in there.

1469
01:16:28.799 --> 01:16:30.032
- (SIGHS)
- Yeah!

1470
01:16:30.034 --> 01:16:32.437
- (ALL GRUNTING)
- Take that!

1471
01:16:38.175 --> 01:16:39.275
(ROARS)

1472
01:16:39.277 --> 01:16:41.313
(GROANS):
Ah.

1473
01:16:42.412 --> 01:16:43.447
(LAUGHS)

1474
01:16:44.381 --> 01:16:45.983
(SCREAMS)

1475
01:16:47.985 --> 01:16:49.854
(PANTING. GRUNTING)

1476
01:16:52.389 --> 01:16:54.222
(GASPS. WHISTLES)

1477
01:16:54.224 --> 01:16:55.160
(SHOUTS)

1478
01:16:57.228 --> 01:16:59.127
(ROARING)

1479
01:16:59.129 --> 01:17:00.328
- Watch out!
- The dragons are everywhere!

1480
01:17:00.330 --> 01:17:02.096
- Incoming!
- Here they come!

1481
01:17:02.098 --> 01:17:04.566
- (SHOUTING CONTINUES)
- Incoming!

1482
01:17:04.568 --> 01:17:06.101
Take cover!

1483
01:17:06.103 --> 01:17:08.337
Where are you going?!

1484
01:17:08.339 --> 01:17:09.808
(BOTH GRUNTING)

1485
01:17:12.043 --> 01:17:14.843
- Heads up!
- (GUARD SCREAMS) - Thanks.

1486
01:17:14.845 --> 01:17:15.781
Look out! (GRUNTS)

1487
01:17:18.915 --> 01:17:20.851
Thanks.

1488
01:17:22.085 --> 01:17:24.021
(GRUNTING CONFUSEDLY)

1489
01:17:27.023 --> 01:17:28.959
(SHOUTING FRANTICALLY)

1490
01:17:31.228 --> 01:17:32.927
(WHISTLES)

1491
01:17:32.929 --> 01:17:35.364
(STORMFLY SQUAWKS)

1492
01:17:35.366 --> 01:17:36.468
(HICCUP GRUNTS)

1493
01:17:39.036 --> 01:17:41.502
(GRUNTING. DRAGON ROARS)

1494
01:17:41.504 --> 01:17:43.605
(SHOUTS)

1495
01:17:43.607 --> 01:17:45.975
(GRUNTS. PANTS)

1496
01:17:45.977 --> 01:17:48.077
I'm coming. Toothless!

1497
01:17:48.079 --> 01:17:51.180
You still think
he cares about you?

1498
01:17:51.182 --> 01:17:52.547
(GRIMMEL GRUNTS.
LIGHT FURY GROWLING)

1499
01:17:52.549 --> 01:17:56.387
Let's just see who he follows.

1500
01:17:58.222 --> 01:18:01.226
(TOOTHLESS ROARING)

1501
01:18:05.329 --> 01:18:08.497
(GRUNTING)

1502
01:18:08.499 --> 01:18:10.632
I'm sorry. bud. for everything.

1503
01:18:10.634 --> 01:18:12.635
(TOOTHLESS PURRS)

1504
01:18:12.637 --> 01:18:14.572
(DRAGONS SQUAWKING)

1505
01:18:20.010 --> 01:18:21.278
(TOOTHLESS GRUNTS)

1506
01:18:27.518 --> 01:18:29.685
(ROARS)

1507
01:18:29.687 --> 01:18:31.622
Now. let's go get her.

1508
01:18:35.125 --> 01:18:37.525
- (YELLING)
- Woo-hoo! Yeah!

1509
01:18:37.527 --> 01:18:39.060
Number two coming through!

1510
01:18:39.062 --> 01:18:40.628
Surprise!

1511
01:18:40.630 --> 01:18:42.096
Sorry about that.

1512
01:18:42.098 --> 01:18:44.065
Come on. (GRUNTS)

1513
01:18:44.067 --> 01:18:45.467
(GUARDS SHOUTING.
DRAGON ROARING)

1514
01:18:45.469 --> 01:18:49.437
- All right!
- One more free! Four to go!

1515
01:18:49.439 --> 01:18:51.306
(FISHLEGS GRUNTS.
GUARD SCREAMS)

1516
01:18:51.308 --> 01:18:53.342
- Try to keep up!
- (GUARDS CHUCKLING)

1517
01:18:53.344 --> 01:18:55.644
I got your backs. Oh!

1518
01:18:55.646 --> 01:18:57.178
(GUARD SCREAMS. WATER SPLASHES)

1519
01:18:57.180 --> 01:19:00.248
Yeah. it's almost like
we're a team. (GASPS)

1520
01:19:00.250 --> 01:19:03.151
(FISHMEAT SQUEALS.
TRAPPER CHUCKLES)

1521
01:19:03.153 --> 01:19:06.187
- You brought a baby to a battle.
- (GROWLS)

1522
01:19:06.189 --> 01:19:09.257
Ah-ah-ah. I wouldn't
do that if I were you.

1523
01:19:09.259 --> 01:19:11.195
(DRAGON ROARING. TRAPPER GASPS)

1524
01:19:12.429 --> 01:19:13.999
(TRAPPER SCREAMS)

1525
01:19:15.332 --> 01:19:17.369
(SHOUTS)

1526
01:19:19.135 --> 01:19:21.602
- God. I love that dragon.
- (FISHMEAT SQUAWKS)

1527
01:19:21.604 --> 01:19:24.739
- (GUARDS CLAMORING)
- Come on! Come back here!

1528
01:19:24.741 --> 01:19:26.708
(GROWLING)

1529
01:19:26.710 --> 01:19:28.711
Sorry we're late for the party.

1530
01:19:28.713 --> 01:19:30.548
You're right on time.

1531
01:19:32.215 --> 01:19:34.350
(THUNDER CRACKING)

1532
01:19:34.352 --> 01:19:36.618
(GROWLS. GROANS)

1533
01:19:36.620 --> 01:19:39.053
(TOOTHLESS ROARS)

1534
01:19:39.055 --> 01:19:40.254
(GROWLS)

1535
01:19:40.256 --> 01:19:42.294
That's it. That's it.

1536
01:19:50.701 --> 01:19:53.267
(LIGHT FURY GROANS)

1537
01:19:53.269 --> 01:19:56.004
How are we gonna get him off
her back without hurting her?

1538
01:19:56.006 --> 01:19:58.340
- Fear the facial hair!
- (GUARD GRUNTS)

1539
01:19:58.342 --> 01:20:00.409
(GRUNTS)

1540
01:20:00.411 --> 01:20:01.743
(SCREAMS)

1541
01:20:01.745 --> 01:20:03.345
(YELLING WILDLY)

1542
01:20:03.347 --> 01:20:05.250
(GASPING. SCREAMING)

1543
01:20:07.250 --> 01:20:08.784
- Oh. I have missed this.
- Me. too.

1544
01:20:08.786 --> 01:20:10.785
- Oh!
- (GRUNTS. LAUGHS)

1545
01:20:10.787 --> 01:20:12.387
Ooh. See that there?

1546
01:20:12.389 --> 01:20:14.422
Aw. Cute.

1547
01:20:14.424 --> 01:20:17.226
That's a bad omen.
You're cursed. (LAUGHS)

1548
01:20:17.228 --> 01:20:18.761
(HOBGOBBLERS SQUEALING.
RAGNAR GASPS)

1549
01:20:18.763 --> 01:20:21.730
(SCREAMING)

1550
01:20:21.732 --> 01:20:23.364
(HOBGOBBLERS SNARLING)

1551
01:20:23.366 --> 01:20:25.133
Yes! Go on!

1552
01:20:25.135 --> 01:20:26.401
Good on you!

1553
01:20:26.403 --> 01:20:28.736
(LAUGHS) I guess you're not
so bad after all.

1554
01:20:28.738 --> 01:20:29.805
(GROWLING)

1555
01:20:29.807 --> 01:20:31.739
(ASTRID CLEARS THROAT.
GUARD GASPS)

1556
01:20:31.741 --> 01:20:33.210
(GUARD SIGHS)

1557
01:20:36.179 --> 01:20:38.113
(GRUNTS)

1558
01:20:38.115 --> 01:20:40.050
(GUARDS SCREAMING
AND CLAMORING)

1559
01:20:44.088 --> 01:20:45.456
(GASPING)

1560
01:20:51.394 --> 01:20:53.428
GUARD:
Abandon ship!

1561
01:20:53.430 --> 01:20:55.297
- (SCREAMING)
- Whoa!

1562
01:20:55.299 --> 01:20:56.364
(GASPING)

1563
01:20:56.366 --> 01:20:57.302
(SCREAMS)

1564
01:21:00.170 --> 01:21:02.738
(GRUNTING)

1565
01:21:02.740 --> 01:21:04.105
- Yay!
- Oh. that was awesome!

1566
01:21:04.107 --> 01:21:07.176
- (LAUGHS)
- Yeah! (WHOOPING)

1567
01:21:07.178 --> 01:21:09.613
♪ ♪

1568
01:21:11.714 --> 01:21:14.651
- (DRAGON ROARS)
- Uh. we've got problems.

1569
01:21:24.161 --> 01:21:26.097
(ROARING)

1570
01:21:29.366 --> 01:21:32.570
- HOARK: Take him down. Hiccup!
- (CROWD CHEERING)

1571
01:21:35.339 --> 01:21:36.441
(ROARING)

1572
01:21:38.476 --> 01:21:40.344
(TAIL RATTLES. TOOTHLESS ROARS)

1573
01:21:41.644 --> 01:21:44.415
We need a better plan.
and quick!

1574
01:21:48.786 --> 01:21:51.220
Uh. uh. what are.
what are you doing?

1575
01:21:51.222 --> 01:21:54.623
- (ELECTRICITY CRACKLING)
- Okay. Okay.

1576
01:21:54.625 --> 01:21:57.328
(ROARING LOUDLY)

1577
01:22:01.331 --> 01:22:03.364
(CROWD GASPING AND MURMURING)

1578
01:22:03.366 --> 01:22:04.867
MAN:
Where has he gone?

1579
01:22:04.869 --> 01:22:08.270
(DRAGONS SQUEALING)

1580
01:22:08.272 --> 01:22:10.842
(ELECTRICITY CRACKLES.
TOOTHLESS ROARS)

1581
01:22:11.875 --> 01:22:13.378
(YELLS)

1582
01:22:15.312 --> 01:22:16.247
(GROANS)

1583
01:22:17.313 --> 01:22:18.747
(GRIMMEL SCREAMS)

1584
01:22:18.749 --> 01:22:20.248
(BOTH GRUNTING)

1585
01:22:20.250 --> 01:22:21.749
You'll kill both of us!

1586
01:22:21.751 --> 01:22:24.218
Fighting over a dragon?

1587
01:22:24.220 --> 01:22:25.654
That's your plan?

1588
01:22:25.656 --> 01:22:26.791
(TOOTHLESS GROANING)

1589
01:22:28.692 --> 01:22:31.293
This is.

1590
01:22:31.295 --> 01:22:32.560
(GRUNTS. SIGHS)

1591
01:22:32.562 --> 01:22:34.428
(LIGHT FURY GROANS)

1592
01:22:34.430 --> 01:22:36.366
Save him.

1593
01:22:40.905 --> 01:22:42.840
(CALLS)

1594
01:22:53.717 --> 01:22:56.286
♪ ♪

1595
01:23:07.764 --> 01:23:10.134
(SHRIEKING)

1596
01:23:12.503 --> 01:23:14.805
(SCREAMS) No!

1597
01:23:18.275 --> 01:23:20.508
(GRUNTS HAPPILY)

1598
01:23:20.510 --> 01:23:21.909
See? (CHUCKLES)

1599
01:23:21.911 --> 01:23:24.281
I knew you'd come around.

1600
01:23:29.586 --> 01:23:31.953
(GRUNTING)

1601
01:23:31.955 --> 01:23:33.888
(PANTING)

1602
01:23:33.890 --> 01:23:35.826
(DRAGONS CALLING)

1603
01:23:40.763 --> 01:23:43.864
(CROWD CHEERING)

1604
01:23:43.866 --> 01:23:45.702
Yeah!

1605
01:23:56.379 --> 01:23:57.681
(HICCUP GRUNTS)

1606
01:23:59.950 --> 01:24:01.949
Hey. Good morning. bud.

1607
01:24:01.951 --> 01:24:03.952
(TOOTHLESS GROANING SOFTLY)

1608
01:24:03.954 --> 01:24:06.555
Here you go.

1609
01:24:06.557 --> 01:24:09.358
Boy. you're full of surprises.

1610
01:24:09.360 --> 01:24:10.758
(LIGHT FURY COOING)

1611
01:24:10.760 --> 01:24:13.794
He's all yours.

1612
01:24:13.796 --> 01:24:15.599
(CHEERING CONTINUES
IN DISTANCE)

1613
01:24:17.668 --> 01:24:19.603
(TOOTHLESS PURRS)

1614
01:24:22.973 --> 01:24:24.940
(BOTH LAUGH)

1615
01:24:24.942 --> 01:24:27.542
You know. Eret may be
blessed with brawn.

1616
01:24:27.544 --> 01:24:31.445
but. just between us.
you have the brains.

1617
01:24:31.447 --> 01:24:33.715
Number one.

1618
01:24:33.717 --> 01:24:35.652
♪ ♪

1619
01:24:41.625 --> 01:24:43.561
(BOTH PURRING)

1620
01:24:47.865 --> 01:24:49.334
(SNIFFS SOFTLY)

1621
01:25:01.978 --> 01:25:05.513
(TOOTHLESS GRUNTING SADLY)

1622
01:25:05.515 --> 01:25:08.385
You're right. bud.
It's time.

1623
01:25:10.054 --> 01:25:14.922
I was so busy fighting for
a world that I wanted.

1624
01:25:14.924 --> 01:25:17.961
I didn't think about
what you needed.

1625
01:25:21.064 --> 01:25:24.666
You've looked after us
for long enough.

1626
01:25:24.668 --> 01:25:26.838
Time to look after yourselves.

1627
01:25:35.411 --> 01:25:36.680
(STORMFLY SNORTS SOFTLY)

1628
01:25:40.483 --> 01:25:43.819
Oh. Stormfly. my good girl.

1629
01:25:43.821 --> 01:25:45.087
All right. Grumpy.

1630
01:25:45.089 --> 01:25:48.090
- (GRUMP PURRS)
- Off you go.

1631
01:25:48.092 --> 01:25:51.392
So long. you big ugly beast.

1632
01:25:51.394 --> 01:25:52.593
I'll miss you.

1633
01:25:52.595 --> 01:25:54.531
(FISHMEAT PANTING)

1634
01:25:55.799 --> 01:25:58.800
♪ ♪

1635
01:25:58.802 --> 01:26:01.403
(WARBLES)

1636
01:26:01.405 --> 01:26:04.008
- Oh. Cloudjumper. Oh.
- (GRUNTS SOFTLY)

1637
01:26:12.750 --> 01:26:14.749
Go on. bud.

1638
01:26:14.751 --> 01:26:16.918
Lead them to the Hidden World.

1639
01:26:16.920 --> 01:26:18.854
(PURRS)

1640
01:26:18.856 --> 01:26:21.056
You'll be safe there.

1641
01:26:21.058 --> 01:26:24.559
Safer than you could
ever be with me.

1642
01:26:24.561 --> 01:26:25.726
(GRUNTS)

1643
01:26:25.728 --> 01:26:27.729
It's okay.
I love you. too.

1644
01:26:27.731 --> 01:26:29.431
And I want you to be free.

1645
01:26:29.433 --> 01:26:31.869
(GROANS SOFTLY)

1646
01:26:33.103 --> 01:26:35.803
Our world doesn't deserve you.

1647
01:26:35.805 --> 01:26:37.075
Yet.

1648
01:26:41.411 --> 01:26:43.347
(PURRING)

1649
01:26:48.485 --> 01:26:49.920
Go. Toothless.

1650
01:26:51.988 --> 01:26:53.624
Go.

1651
01:26:56.893 --> 01:26:58.829
♪ ♪

1652
01:27:06.570 --> 01:27:07.903
(ROARING LOUDLY)

1653
01:27:07.905 --> 01:27:10.907
(DRAGONS ROARING)

1654
01:27:16.513 --> 01:27:17.782
(LIGHT FURY PURRS)

1655
01:27:23.954 --> 01:27:27.125
(CROWD MURMURING)

1656
01:27:32.830 --> 01:27:34.765
(DRAGONS CALLING)

1657
01:27:36.467 --> 01:27:39.704
♪ ♪

1658
01:27:58.722 --> 01:28:00.892
(GRUNTS SOFTLY)

1659
01:28:05.862 --> 01:28:07.798
♪ ♪

1660
01:28:25.883 --> 01:28:27.818
♪ ♪

1661
01:28:38.594 --> 01:28:40.530
(SHEEP BLEATING SOFTLY)

1662
01:28:47.905 --> 01:28:49.840
♪ ♪

1663
01:29:13.696 --> 01:29:16.534
(SNIFFLING)

1664
01:29:19.902 --> 01:29:22.636
SPITELOUT:
To the chief and chieftess!

1665
01:29:22.638 --> 01:29:25.205
- Yeah!
- (CROWD CHEERING)

1666
01:29:25.207 --> 01:29:27.108
PHLEGMA:
Good on you!

1667
01:29:27.110 --> 01:29:30.578
Come. cry into
my full. thick beard.

1668
01:29:30.580 --> 01:29:32.846
(SOBBING):
It's so beautiful!

1669
01:29:32.848 --> 01:29:35.083
- Gross.
- (SOBBING)

1670
01:29:35.085 --> 01:29:37.252
Okay. you win.

1671
01:29:37.254 --> 01:29:39.753
I like sensitive guys.

1672
01:29:39.755 --> 01:29:41.590
HOARK: I thought
it would never happen.

1673
01:29:41.592 --> 01:29:43.123
Finally. right? (LAUGHS)

1674
01:29:43.125 --> 01:29:45.126
(CHEERING CONTINUES)

1675
01:29:45.128 --> 01:29:47.063
♪ ♪

1676
01:30:08.919 --> 01:30:10.854
(WIND WHISTLING SOFTLY)

1677
01:30:13.357 --> 01:30:15.990
HICCUP: <i>There were dragons
when I was a boy.</i>

1678
01:30:15.992 --> 01:30:18.993
(SNIFFLES)

1679
01:30:18.995 --> 01:30:21.328
<i>Ah. there were
great. grim sky dragons</i>

1680
01:30:21.330 --> 01:30:25.400
<i>that nested on the clifftops
like gigantic. scary birds.</i>

1681
01:30:25.402 --> 01:30:26.767
(WATER SPLASHES)

1682
01:30:26.769 --> 01:30:28.235
<i>Little. brown. scuttly dragons</i>

1683
01:30:28.237 --> 01:30:32.841
<i>that hunted down the mice and
rats in well-organized packs.</i>

1684
01:30:32.843 --> 01:30:35.275
<i>Preposterously huge sea dragons</i>

1685
01:30:35.277 --> 01:30:40.248
<i>that were 20 times as big
as the big blue whale.</i>

1686
01:30:40.250 --> 01:30:42.751
<i>Some say they crawled
back into the sea.</i>

1687
01:30:42.753 --> 01:30:46.354
<i>leaving not a bone nor a fang
for men to remember them by.</i>

1688
01:30:46.356 --> 01:30:51.059
<i>Others say they were nothing
but folktales to begin with.</i>

1689
01:30:51.061 --> 01:30:53.598
<i>Ah. I'm okay with that.</i>

1690
01:31:14.750 --> 01:31:16.818
Hey.

1691
01:31:16.820 --> 01:31:19.156
Hey there. bud.

1692
01:31:25.728 --> 01:31:27.231
Remember me?

1693
01:31:29.700 --> 01:31:31.335
- It's okay.
- (GASPS)

1694
01:31:33.437 --> 01:31:35.904
(SNIFFS)

1695
01:31:35.906 --> 01:31:37.905
(TOOTHLESS GRUNTS HAPPILY.
HICCUP LAUGHING)

1696
01:31:37.907 --> 01:31:40.975
(LAUGHS. SIGHS)

1697
01:31:40.977 --> 01:31:44.945
Hey. I am glad
to see you. too. bud. (GRUNTS)

1698
01:31:44.947 --> 01:31:47.382
He's not gonna eat your father.

1699
01:31:47.384 --> 01:31:49.383
(LAUGHS):
Hey!

1700
01:31:49.385 --> 01:31:51.218
How's the tail holding up?

1701
01:31:51.220 --> 01:31:53.053
Probably could use some oil
and a little fine-tuning.

1702
01:31:53.055 --> 01:31:55.989
Look. it's okay.
They're friends.

1703
01:31:55.991 --> 01:31:58.193
(LAUGHING)

1704
01:31:58.195 --> 01:32:01.428
(GROANS) Cut it out.

1705
01:32:01.430 --> 01:32:02.830
Here.

1706
01:32:02.832 --> 01:32:04.466
Go on. It's all right.

1707
01:32:04.468 --> 01:32:06.400
Come.

1708
01:32:06.402 --> 01:32:08.837
He won't hurt you.

1709
01:32:08.839 --> 01:32:10.504
Hold your hands out.

1710
01:32:10.506 --> 01:32:13.041
Like this.

1711
01:32:13.043 --> 01:32:14.945
That's it.

1712
01:32:17.347 --> 01:32:19.884
Let him come to you.

1713
01:32:23.152 --> 01:32:24.485
(PURRING SOFTLY)

1714
01:32:24.487 --> 01:32:27.288
(BOTH GASP)

1715
01:32:27.290 --> 01:32:29.226
♪ ♪

1716
01:32:39.936 --> 01:32:41.171
(LAUGHS)

1717
01:32:43.272 --> 01:32:45.140
(LAUGHS)

1718
01:32:45.142 --> 01:32:47.342
(TOOTHLESS GRUNTS)

1719
01:32:47.344 --> 01:32:49.280
(ROARING)

1720
01:32:51.281 --> 01:32:53.217
(LAUGHS)

1721
01:32:57.454 --> 01:32:59.389
(BABY DRAGONS CHITTERING)

1722
01:33:08.130 --> 01:33:09.329
(SQUEAKING)

1723
01:33:09.331 --> 01:33:10.330
(ASTRID WHOOPS)

1724
01:33:10.332 --> 01:33:13.267
(ASTRID LAUGHS. GIRL LAUGHS)

1725
01:33:13.269 --> 01:33:15.270
HICCUP:
<i>Legend says that</i>

1726
01:33:15.272 --> 01:33:18.038
<i>when the ground quakes
or lava spews from the earth.</i>

1727
01:33:18.040 --> 01:33:23.144
<i>it's the dragons. letting us
know they're still here.</i>

1728
01:33:23.146 --> 01:33:26.082
<i>waiting for us to figure out
how to get along.</i>

1729
01:33:30.053 --> 01:33:31.856
(STORMFLY SQUAWKS)

1730
01:33:33.589 --> 01:33:36.591
<i>Yes. the world believes
the dragons are gone.</i>

1731
01:33:36.593 --> 01:33:39.293
<i>if they ever existed at all.</i>

1732
01:33:39.295 --> 01:33:44.298
<i>But we Berkians.
we know otherwise.</i>

1733
